 for bestpractices and # Audit Trail & Compliance

## Overview
Implement a robust, immutable audit trail system to capture all critical actions across AquaTrace: reads, writes, approvals, downloads, exports, and sign-offs. Provide append-only logging with secure storage, retention policies, tamper-evidence, and optional digital signing. Expose a searchable Audit Viewer in the admin UI, with role-based access control and export capabilities. Integrate with the Lab Manager Dashboard (Approval Queue) to log approvals, rejections, and distribution of reports as part of the workflow. Ensure the system supports 5 user roles (Technician, Lab Tech, Lab Manager, Administration, Viewer) and adheres to compliance requirements.

---

## Components to Build

- Audit Log Service (Backend)
  - Append-only log storage (immutable by design, supporting time-based retention)
  - User, timestamp, action type, target resource, metadata
  - Digital signing/tamper-evidence for sensitive entries
  - Retention policies, export (CSV/JSON/PDF) capabilities
  - Tamper-detection: hash chaining, ETag checks, or Merkle-like structure if feasible

- Audit Trail API (Backend)
  - Create log entry (write)
  - Query logs (filters: date range, user, actionType, resource, customer, case ID)
  - Export logs (downloadable archive)
  - Get audit summary/metrics (counts by action/type)
  - Validation: ensure fields exist and are properly typed; guard against null/undefined results

- Audit Viewer (Frontend)
  - Admin UI page to search, filter, sort, paginate audit entries
  - Real-time-ish updates (polling or websocket) for new entries if enabled
  - Export controls (CSV/JSON)
  - Safety: handle potential null data safely, provide default empty arrays

- Lab Manager Dashboard (Approval Queue) Integration
  - Log actions when approvals are submitted, rejections, sign-offs
  - Log distribution events (PDF generation, email/send-to-customer)
  - Sign-off events tied to specific reports
  - Ensure actions are auditable even when offline or on mobile

- Data Model Migrations
  - AuditEntry table/schema with immutable intent
  - Indexes on user, actionType, resourceId, timestamp for efficient查询
  - Relationship to resource tables (tests, reports, PDFs, customers)

- Security & Compliance
  - Role-based access control (RBAC) for read/write/audit
  - Ensure only authenticated users can create logs
  - Digital signatures for sensitive actions
  - Data encryption at rest and in transit (where applicable)

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Audit Viewer Page (admin UI)
  - Components:
    - AuditTable: displays logs with columns (timestamp, user, actionType, resource, metadata summary)
    - FilterBar: date range picker, user select, action type multi-select, resource type, search keyword
    - PaginationControls
    - ExportButton: triggers API export (CSV/JSON)
    - DetailPane: expandable row to view full metadata and audit trail hash/signature
  - Interactions:
    - Safe rendering: guard against non-array data; use (data ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(data) ? data.map(...) : []
    - Debounced search, server-side filtering
    - Keyboard accessible controls; responsive layout
  - Data handling:
    - Fetch logs via GET /api/audit/logs?filters=...
    - Ensure response shapes validated: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
    - Default state initialization: useState<AuditEntry[]>([])

- Lab Manager Dashboard (Approval Queue)
  - Actions to log:
    - Approve test results
    - Reject test results
    - Sign-off report
    - Distribute/export report (PDF) to customer
  - UI elements:
    - ApprovalQueueTable with rows representing completed tests awaiting approval
    - Action buttons per row: Approve, Reject, Sign-off, Distribute
    - Confirmation dialogs and failure handling
  - Logging hooks:
    - On assign/approve/reject/sign-off, call auditLogService.createLog with: userId, actionType, resourceType (Report/Test), resourceId, metadata (testId, customerId, notes, version, pdfHash)
  - Data safety:
    - Guard all potential null values; use (items ?? []).map(...)
    - Initialize state with proper types: useState<ApprovalItem[]>([])

- Admin/Settings Integration
  - Ensure audit log viewing is accessible to Admin role only
  - Administrative export of logs with restricted data masking if needed

---

### Backend
- API Endpoints
  - POST /api/audit/logs
    - Create an audit entry
    - Body: { userId, actionType, resourceType, resourceId, metadata: object, signed?: boolean, signature?: string }
    - Validation: non-empty userId, actionType, resourceType, resourceId; metadata object
  - GET /api/audit/logs
    - Query params: from, to, userId, actionTypes[], resourceTypes[], resourceIds[], q (search)
    - Returns: { data: AuditEntry[], total: number }
  - GET /api/audit/logs/export
    - Similar filters; returns downloadable file (CSV/JSON)
  - GET /api/audit/summary
    - Returns counts by actionType, date ranges, top resources
- Data Models
  - AuditEntry
    - id: string (UUID)
    - userId: string
    - userName?: string
    - actionType: string (enum: READ, WRITE, APPROVE, REJECT, DOWNLOAD, SIGN_OFF, EXPORT)
    - resourceType: string (e.g., TEST_RESULT, REPORT, PDF, CUSTOMER_RECORD)
    - resourceId: string
    - timestamp: string (ISO)
    - metadata: JSONB
    - hash: string (for tamper-evidence)
    - previousHash?: string
    - signature?: string (digital signature for tamper-evidence)
  - Indexes: on timestamp (DESC), userId, actionType, resourceType, resourceId
- Database
  - PostgreSQL (or existing DB)
  - Ensure append-only semantics; do not update rows, only insert
  - Migration scripts to create AuditEntry table and indices
- Services / Business Logic
